snippet.textDisplay: Thank you brother. Im a Marine combat vet. Did 2 tours to Iraq, seen and done all kinds of violence, seen brothers die, seen innocent people killed, i was heartless and ruthless. Today is 15 years since my boy got killed the week before we got to Iraq. The last words i said to him before they left for their deployment was, "I'll see you when we get there dude. Stay safe." Then all the stuff after my time in the military. 2 failed engagements, broken relationships, an ex fiance hung herself 3 years ago, forced relationship the week after i found out she died. Then last year God brought the woman into my life who He commanded me to love. She's broken from trauma too. God used me to bless her. Being selfless ain't easy, but it's not meant to be. I relate to the cop in the video. Different battlefields, same pain. Thank you man. God bless you. Praying for you dude. I had tears bro.

Stayed up late patiently waiting
Wishing you could call
Dreaming of memories lost in time
Knowing they're all gone
So I take this bottle and drown my sorrows
And throw it against the wall
The higher you fly
The harder you fall
Till there's nothing left at all

Four in the morning I cannot sleep
I am depressed sitting up in my bed
The demons are roaring they're bothering me
I'm sitting here with a gun to my head
Finger on trigger, what if I squeezed?
Does that mean that my problems will leave?
Get rid of what's bothering me?
Does that mean that I'm finally free
I think of my daughter I think of my wife
I think of my brothers I think of my life
I can't leave them with bad news
My life is a crap-shoot
I'm just shaking the dice
Had a dream last night (Had a dream last night)
I can hear you say (I can hear you say)
Son just be strong (Son just be strong)
You gon' be okay (You gon' be okay)
Tell the truth, I don't feel that way
I still feel fucked up to this day
Even when I'm high I just sit and cry
And wonder why I still feel this pain
I wish Heaven wasn't so far away
I wish I could visit just for a day
I still had so much left to say
Bow our heads and let us pray

I feel like my past will allow me to grow
Feel like this liquor is drowning my soul
Why am I spiraling out of control?
I cannot get myself out of this hole
I keep trying, I keep crawling
The sound of silence, I hear it calling
I was flying, now I'm falling
My health declining, I'm an alcoholic
There's no one else, it's just myself
Alone in thought, I stand and dwell
I'm the go-to guy, so who do I
So who do I go to when I need some help?
No one gives a fuck about me, I'm on my own
If misery loves company then why am I alone?
I pour another drink just to get in my zone
I swear that I'ma change, but I know that I won't
Let me face the facts (Face the facts)
Wish I could take it back (Take it back)
Wish I could fade to black (Fade to black)
Wish I could change the past (Change the past)
But in my mind I wish that I could rewind
Press pause and live my life inside a moment of time
But I can't

snippet.textDisplay: This song struck me, it had me feeling a roller coaster of emotions. At the time my Dad passed away I was between jobs and I used alcohol as a crutch to get through life problems. I thought during this time it would be a great idea to buy a still. Being the oldest brother and now the person everyone looked to because my Dad wasn't here no more started to take its toll. At the same time, I know he wouldn't want to see me like that so I did my best to put it back together. This song really took me back to those moments and days. It's crazy you could capture that all in a song.

This song hit me hard. I lost my son 7 years ago on my birthday. I was so lost and angry. I lost my gym my fight team my world. I met a women who saved me from the darkness that I was engulfed in. I started drinking bad. Something I didnt do. Owning a mma gym I tried to set a good example for my students but the pain was so hard to bare. She saved my life for real. I still hurt every day and cry all the time. But I fi ally got help. I know I will never be the same man I was cause the day he died a piece of me did. But I also know my now wife was eight when she told me my son Xander wouldn't wont me to become something I hated and my nana either. Getting g helped was the best thing g I've ever done. I have a long way to go but I get there daily. If you need help reach out to me. I will help anyway I can. Dhardy413@yahoo.com or find someone that you talk too. If you know someone that needs help keep reaching out to them. Many times my best friend saved me from ending my life because he stopped by without notice to check on me. My wife let's me cry on her lap and always tells me when I try to hold back the tears to just let it out. We need to help one another. I dont care what the issue is. I'm here if anyone needs anything.

snippet.textDisplay: When all you wanted from the time you were a boy was true love and someone to share this journey with and have the honor to grow old and gray with, and each time you fail, and you realize the fault lies in you until the day your 34 and you finally meet her your soulmate and you just know it. Undeniable. But she never sees it. And you chase her for year-and-a-half, learning her story and growing to know everything about her all of her tendencies, knowing when something was wrong before she told you, to finishing her sentences. The ups and downs of trying to get with her and always failing and then one day you give up your back off. Then a miracle happened. She started missing you and the next thing you know you come together. Afterlife of love lost and failure that led to numbing the pain with whatever drug possible you finally pulled it off and you felt complete & Free. You bury your past and your pain and the drugs away. you finally did it you had what you've always wanted and then out of the blue 2 months later she just disappears ghost you for no reason and this is the one that hurts the most because this is the one where it wasn't my fault. I was writing a love story and it was beautiful because I had written too many tragedies. Now 38 years old a year-and-a-half later, strung out on crystal numbing with whiskey just trying to leave this place as soon as I can. and in your heart of hearts you know that that's not how the story should have ended and you never got answers and you'll never be able to love again because there will never be another like her because you never thought you would find her to begin with. I never got the chance to love her back to life like she did me. I had so many plans for her I was going to give her back all of her hopes and dreams. I work so hard and I was at the best position I've ever been in my life. I was finally alive no chains bound me anymore and the world stole her. This song made me cry so hard which I cry every night anyways. But this is so deep. I don't want to be doing this drowning in whiskey and dancing with Crystal anymore. I want my heart and soul back the one that my heart yearns for the one that took me 34 years to meet my soulmate the one that was going to be my wife. the one I was going to give her dream wedding on the beach to which was also where I wanted to have my dream wedding. A man of love the most sacred thing, a man that's old-fashioned and still upholds the way a man is supposed to treat a woman. But a man whose only dream is what killed him. I would do anything just to see her one more time. just that true happiness that I never thought I would and then did. To stop time and hold her in my arms again and sing her love songs. To protect her from ever having to worry about another man ever abusing her again which is why I know the world put us together to begin with. she was the woman that took everything I had inside of me and put it together to become the man I was meant to be the man meant to love her, the one that made me complete my rock. the woman that deep down inside just wanted to be Cinderella and her prince charming well she had it but because of her awful past and terrible men instead of seeing what she had in front of her and looking to the future I guess all she could see was the past and it made her run away. I never got the time needed. I never got to have the forever I always wanted just as she always wanted. The world ain't right when it's so obvious two people belong together but it takes it away for no reason. And now as I'm writing this drowning in the bottle while also floating in the clouds. Halfway in the grave, tears in my eyes, she's the only thing on my mind. The only thing that can save me. And if In meant to be alive much longer maybe the world will make it right. Thank you for this beautiful piece of music. I'm glad my ears got to hear before I pass on from this completely shattered heart. I love you Jenifer Ann McGhee. The pain and the yearning of my heart to love but not having you is the worst pain I've ever felt.
